# Step 6

Create a new screen:

```text
lib/screens/backend_test_screen.dart
```

Paste:

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

import '../api/api_service.dart';

class BackendTestScreen extends StatefulWidget {

  const BackendTestScreen({super.key});

  @override
  State<BackendTestScreen> createState() =>
      _BackendTestScreenState();

}

class _BackendTestScreenState
    extends State<BackendTestScreen> {

  String status = "Checking...";

  @override
  void initState() {

    super.initState();

    loadStatus();

  }

  Future<void> loadStatus() async {

    ApiService api = ApiService();

    String result = await api.checkBackend();

    setState(() {

      status = result;

    });

  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {

    return Scaffold(

      appBar: AppBar(

        title: const Text("Backend Test"),

      ),

      body: Center(

        child: Text(

          status,

          style: const TextStyle(

            fontSize: 28,

            fontWeight: FontWeight.bold,

          ),

        ),

      ),

    );

  }

}
```

---

# Step 7

Temporarily change your `main.dart` so it starts with:

```dart
home: const BackendTestScreen(),
```

instead of your normal home screen.

Don't forget to import it:

```dart
import 'screens/backend_test_screen.dart';
```

---

# Step 8

Run the backend:

```bash
uvicorn main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0
```

Notice the difference from yesterday.

Yesterday we used:

```bash
uvicorn main:app --reload
```

Today we use:

```bash
uvicorn main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0
```

This allows devices on your local network (like your phone) to reach your backend.

---

# Step 9

Run Flutter:

```bash
flutter run
```

If everything is configured correctly, your phone should display:

```text
Healthy
```

🎉 That means your Flutter app successfully contacted your FastAPI backend.

